Annotation

Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
Laboratory results are largely within normal limits. Notable findings include mildly low creatinine (likely reflecting low muscle mass), low total cholesterol, high chloride, elevated platelet distribution width, and low mean platelet volume. HbA1c is at the upper end of normal, suggesting good glycemic control. No evidence of anemia, infection, or renal dysfunction. Overall, no acute laboratory concerns; findings should be interpreted in clinical context.
